OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1772499776
OL,3,CBus drivers strike 'will continue' on
OL,4,CFriday if 'serious proposal' is not
OL,5,Cmade
OL,7,FMeanwhile, a spokesperson for the
OL,8,Fgovernment said: 'Bus Vannin remains
OL,9,Fready and willing to have positive and
OL,10,Fconstructive negotiations with Unite
OL,11,Fthe Union and hopes that the Unite's
OL,12,Fstrike on Friday can be avoided.
OL,14,F'Bus Vannin is committed to finding a
OL,15,Ffair resolution to the dispute and its
OL,16,Fsix offers remain on the table as a
OL,17,Fbasis for further discussions.'
OL,19,FUnite say they are ready to meet for
OL,20,Ftalks 'immediately'.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/5
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
